com.xceptance.xlt.ai.corner

Class Fast9

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.xceptance.xlt.ai.corner.Fast9
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICornersFeatureDetector

    public class Fast9
extends java.lang.Object
implements ICornersFeatureDetector
    Features from Accelerated Segment Test (FAST) corners detector. In the FAST corner detection algorithm, a pixel is defined as a corner if (in a circle surrounding the pixel), N or more contiguous pixels are all significantly brighter then or all significantly darker than the center pixel. The ordering of questions used to classify a pixel is learned using the ID3 algorithm. This detector has been shown to exhibit a high degree of repeatability.
    Author:
    Diego Catalano Edited by Thomas Volkmann

      • detect

        private java.util.List<FeaturePoint> detect(FastBitmap fb,
                                            int threshold)
        The detect method gather the information of the surrounding pixels of the center. Therefore it compute the entropy and the information gain for the sets of pixels. The size of this algorithm is the unrolled recursive version of the decision tree, therefore it is a bunch of nested if-else statements.
        Parameters:
        fb - FastBitmap converted BufferedImage
        threshold - considered border
        Returns:
        corners ArrayList of FeaturePoint, all found corners are saved as FeaturePoint
